OL,3,CWhy a gorilla statue could cost
OL,4,Chomeowner #20,000 in planning row
OL,6,FA woman in Wakefield could face a fine
OL,7,Fup to #20,000 if she doesn't remove a
OL,8,Fgorilla statue from the front of her
OL,9,Fhouse.
OL,11,FCaeser, a four foot plastic gorilla,
OL,12,Fis perched on a plinth outside a
OL,13,Fterraced home on Lee Moor Lane, in
OL,14,FStanley.
OL,16,FThe homeowner, Adele Teale, is now
OL,17,Fcaught in the middle of a legal row
OL,18,Fafter someone alerted the council.
OL,20,FShe said the figure is harmless, and
OL,21,Fis a popular feature with locals.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/6
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
